            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I recently used @kaeptmblaubaer1000 's solution with Cython 0.28.4, and it resulted in MSVC's compiler error C3431: `a scoped enumeration cannot be redeclared as an unscoped enumeration` when I tried using it in a `cdef` declaration.\r\n\r\n```\r\ncdef extern from \"headername.h\" namespace \"lol\":\r\n    cdef enum rofl:\r\n        SOMETHING \"lol::rofl::SOMETHING\",\r\n        MOAR \"lol::rofl::MOAR\"\r\n\r\ncdef void lololol():\r\n    cdef rofl moarlol\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe reason is that the enum is declared as `enum class rofl` and Cython generates\r\n\r\n```C++\r\nenum rofl __pyx_v_moarlol;\r\n```\r\n\r\neffectively declaring `rofl` as a regular enum, instead of \r\n\r\n```C++\r\nrofl __pyx_v_moarlol;\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe solution for me was to replace `cdef enum rofl` with `ctypedef enum rofl` which removes the `enum` keyword, as shown here: http://cython.readthedocs.io/en/latest/src/userguide/external_C_code.html#styles-of-struct-union-and-enum-declaration",
